%N A391273 Smallest base b >= 2 for which one "Reverse and Add" step in base b starting from n yields a palindrome in base b.
%C A391273 a(n) must exist and be <= 2*n-1 because "Reverse and Add" of every n equals palindrome "11" in base 2*n-1. In practice, however, palindromes occur due to either the Add step producing no carry or the result comprising only base b digits <= 2, each of which is not uncommon. Consequently, it is observed that a(n) maxima are consistent with probabilistic expectations as a predominantly polylogarithmic function of n, with no a(n) >= 100 for n <= 10^8.
%C A391273 Integers k such that a(k) = 2 are A066122.
%H A391273 Michael S. Branicky, <a href="/A391273/b391273.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 2..10001</a>
%e A391273 a(5) = 4 because 5 = 101_2 and 101_2 + 101_2 = 1010_2 (not a palindrome); 5 = 12_3 and 12_3 + 21_3 = 110_3 (not a palindrome); 5 = 11_4 and 11_4 + 11_4 = 22_4 (IS a palindrome).
%t A391273 a[n_]:=Module[{b=2},While[!PalindromeQ[IntegerDigits[n+FromDigits[Reverse[IntegerDigits[n,b]],b],b]],b++];b];Array[a,87,2] (* _James C. McMahon_, Dec 17 2025 *)
%o A391273 (PARI) a(n)={for(b=2, n*2, my(d=digits(n+fromdigits(Vecrev(digits(n, b)), b), b)); if(d==Vecrev(d), return(b)))}
%o A391273 (Python)
%o A391273 from itertools import count
%o A391273 from sympy.ntheory import digits, is_palindromic
%o A391273 def fromrevdigits(t, b): return sum(b**i*ti for i, ti in enumerate(t))
%o A391273 def a(n): return next(b for b in count(2) if is_palindromic(n+fromrevdigits(digits(n, b)[1:], b), b))
